nt|haans: ty|pg||
nt|flash: Bergen?  nice fellow; lousy convention|pg||
nt|haans: 15 minutes to final session (just for fun)|pg||
nt|flash: the idea behind Bergen is an extension of the Law of Total Tricks - to bid as high as the Law suggests immediately|pg||
nt|flash: so 1M - 3M becomes pre-emptive|pg||
nt|flash: and you need other calls to show the invitational hand|pg||
nt|haans: dont like Bergen style after 1bt-2red Jump to 3 with 4 cards in suit minor hand|pg||
nt|flash: and you can differentiate between a garbage raise and a constructive raise, again based on the number of trumps you hold|pg||
nt|flash: but you give up a lot of constructive bids to squeeze this all in|pg||
nt|flash: i'm an old fogey, and favor old-fashioned limit raises; but i also prefer to have all the other calls available|pg||
